#1601
The Gates of Vingaard Keep~
   You stand before the massive gates of Vingaard Keep.  The walls rise up
about twenty feet above you.  The stone used to make the gate is new and almost
sparkles in the light of day.  The portcullis is closed, and no less than two
guards are posted here at all times for protection.  Looking up, you can see
bright white and purple flags fluttering from the battlements, bearing the
standard of the Knights of Solamnia.  Vingaard has stood for centuries and
despite various attempts, it has never fallen to assault.  It stands here near
the mountains, a mighty bulwark of goodness and virtue.  It serves primarily as
a training ground and fortress for the Knights, though over the years, a number
of civilians have also made it their home, primarily serving the needs of those
posted here: the knights and their families.  As you stand looking, the guards
at the gate begin to eye you.    
~
