In the Tower~
   This room near the top of this stone tower is round, and would be cold and
barren if it weren't for a few rustic touches here and there.  There is a large
bearskin rug spread out on the floor in front of a crackling fire.  There is a
lone desk sitting against the southern wall.  There are better towers in the
keep from which to keep an eye out, so naturally this is not a lookout tower.
In times of war, some archers might be poised here.  This is evidenced by the
presence of murder holes on all sides of the tower.  Currently, it is serving
as the office of a Knight of the Sword, who sits and pores over papers.  He
does not look happy to be here, and perhaps he irked one of his commanders to
be assigned to desk duty.  A set of stone steps leads back down from here.    
